						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1468 (1546 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>States that Śrīraṅgadēvarāyar who was the disciple of Tātāchārya built the <hi rend="italic">garbha-gṛiha, ardha-maṇḍapa, māha-maṇḍapa, gōpura,</hi> etc. at Vāmanakshētra and endowed a village to the same. Gives the epithet Śrīraṅgadēvaśikhāmaṇi to Tātāchārya. Except for the <hi rend="bold">Śaka and the cyclic years viz., 1468, Parābhava,</hi> no other details of the date are given. <hi rend="bold">The year corresponds to 1546. A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>1. Read <hi rend="italic">maº</hi></p>						

						</summary>
